# Project conventions (eveback.local)

## Skills Activation

Domain-specific skills live in `.cursor/skills/`. Activate the relevant skill when working in that domain.

- **Quasar** (`quasar-development`): `QSelect`, `QDialog`, `QBanner`, `useQuasar`, and other Quasar components in `resources/js/`. Not for Blade-only pages or PHP.
- **Laravel** (`laravel-best-practices`): controllers, models, migrations, queries, policies, jobs.

## Quasar + Laravel Architecture

- Laravel Blade gates authentication: authenticated users see the Quasar SPA via `resources/views/home.blade.php`.
- Unauthenticated users are redirected to `/login`.
- The Quasar app boots from `resources/js/app.js` and renders `<app>` in `resources/js/views/App.vue`.
- Use Sanctum for CSRF protection and API authentication.
- API routes in `routes/api.php` should be protected with `auth:sanctum` where appropriate.
- Vue Router routes live in `resources/js/router.js`.
- Pinia store: `resources/js/store/` (and legacy `resources/js/store.js`).
- Components live in `resources/js/components/`; pages in `resources/js/views/`.

## Git hooks (server / any clone)

- This repo ships **`.githooks/post-merge`**: after a successful **`git pull`** (merge), it runs **`composer install --no-interaction`** so `vendor/` matches the committed lockfile.
- One-time setup per clone: `./scripts/install-git-hooks.sh` (sets `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`).
- Do **not** run `composer update` on production servers; updates happen locally before push, then the lock is installed on pull.

## Laravel Boost MCP

- MCP config: `.cursor/mcp.json` (runs via Sail: `vendor/bin/sail artisan boost:mcp`).
- Prefer Boost tools (`search-docs`, `database-schema`, `database-query`, `browser-logs`, `get-absolute-url`) over manual alternatives when available.
- Re-run `vendor/bin/sail artisan boost:install` after major dependency changes if Boost assets need refreshing.
